The paper deals with the recovery of sparse wavelet coefficients in the Fourier domain, which is a problem in signal processing and imaging. The paper also introduces a new ensemble of random bipartite graphs, which is relevant to the analysis of iterative decoding algorithms used in signal recovery. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves numerical experiments and system architecture for MRI, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
